    "created_at": "2018-03-28T12:00:18Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-03-28T12:00:18Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Even though I think the usefulness of this setting is very limited, CARES_ROOT_DIR now seems to be configurable:\r\nhttps://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/31bdbbeacf84d3a1e867e50b312c9cf46afc20db/cmake/cares.cmake\r\n\r\nWhy I think it's not useful:\r\nif you are building with gRPC_CARES_PROVIDER=module, you can easily use the c-ares source code from the git submodule and you don't need to reconfigure CARES_ROOT_DIR.\r\n\r\nIf you are building with gRPC_CARES_PROVIDER=package (and c-ares is preinstalled somewhere on your system via cmake install), you need to use c-ares_DIR variable to configure cmake's find_package( ) to correctly locate c-ares instead.\r\n"
